The paper deals with image processing, specifically denoising and inpainting, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The proposed approach involves ordering patches in high-dimensional space, which could also be related to information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of one-dimensional smoothing operations suggests a connection to multimedia (cs.MM) and numerical analysis (cs.NA).
